Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses power-proportional data centers and their optimization. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new online algorithm based on regularization technique. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the dynamic right-sizing problem for heterogeneous data centers. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a new algorithm for optimizing data center operations. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the optimization of data center operations, which can have implications for network architecture.
